</b></p>
<p> 
<b>43
</b></p>
<p>detention or arrest;  
</p>
<p>&#8226; timely access to counsel;  
&#8226; adequate time and 
facilities to prepare a 
defence; appearance and 
cross-examination of 
witnesses; and 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Ensuring the independence 
and impartiality of the 
judiciary. 
</p>
<p>only after the first interrogation; 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Lack of independence of the 
