provided for in the law, but 
could be partly based on 
Chapter V of the 
Constitution. In practice 
however, lawyers were 
</p>
<p>A National Legal Aid Scheme was pending 
before Parliament. 
</p>
<p><b><i>Non-governmental sources:</i></b><i> Due to the 
extremely high costs of legal aid, it 
remains unavailable to the majority of the 
population.</i> 
