application had to be 
</p>
<p>The Criminal Amendment Act, enacted in 2003, 
abolished corporal punishment as a legal criminal 
penalty and corporal punishment was also 
banished by corporal punishment. 
</p>
<p><b><i>Non-governmental sources:</i></b><i> Kenya retains 
hard labour as a lawful punishment for 
convicted prisoners. </i></p>

