dd.6 
</b></p>
<p><b>154</b> <b>duress; 
</b></p>
<p><b>iii) Judges, prosecutors and medical 
personnel should routinely ask 
persons arriving from police custody 
how they have been treated;  
</b></p>
<p><b>iv) Consider video and audio taping 
interrogations; 
</b></p>
<p><b>v) Regularly and following each 
