</b></p>
<p><b>vii) Ensure that the sound legal basis 
of the National Preventive 
Mechanism (NPM) translates in its 
effective functioning in practice, 
including through allocation of 
budgetary and human resources. 
</b></p>
<p>that judges, prosecutors and other 
actors in the criminal law cycle 
routinely ignored allegations of 
torture;  
</p>
<p>The burden of proof was on the victim; 
</p>
